zipios
------------------------------------------
Zipios is a small C++ library for reading and writing zip files. The structure
and public interface are based (somewhat loosely) on the java.util.zip package.
The streams created to access the individual entries in a zip file are based on
the standard iostream library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  libzipios-devel-2.2.5.0-1bl1
  libzipios2-2.2.5.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1
  zlib0-1.2.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Zipios/Zipios

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Zipios/Zipios/archive/v2.2.5.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack zipios-2.2.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./zipios-2.2.5.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/zipios-2.2.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/zipios-2.2.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libzipios2-2.2.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libzipios-devel-2.2.5.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(zipios)
  /usr/bin/appendzip.exe
  /usr/bin/dosdatetime.exe
  /usr/bin/zipios.exe
